latestPosts.caption:
@letsmeet.tommorow tried the Klairs Midnight Blue Calming Cream and she says:

Wow—my skin literally drinks this up after a long day. 🌙💙 I use it at night whenever my skin feels irritated or red (especially after exfoliating or too much sun), and by morning, everything feels calmer and less inflamed.

The texture is super lightweight but still really soothing, and I love that subtle cooling sensation when it goes on. Plus, the blue color? So satisfying. I don’t use it as a daily moisturizer, more like a calming treatment—and it’s officially a holy grail for my sensitive skin. 🧴✨

(kbeauty, blue cream, calming cream, gel moisturizer for sensitive skin, viral korean skincare)

The Midnight Blue Calming Cream says “Hi!”

Why is it blue?
💙 due to the presence of Guaiazulene
💙 extracted from chamomile oil
💙 gives that beautiful blue hue to the cream
💙 has soothing & anti-inflammatory properties

@itsmedeblinac shares her empty update! 🤍

- - - - - - - -

One of THE MOST gentle cleansing products that I have ever used. 🫶🏻

I often hear that foaming cleansers are too drying. And that can be true sometimes, especially if you don’t foam it up well or have very sensitive skin like mine.

However, you can always trust @dear_klairs when it comes to calming and soothing skincare. As someone who tests a lot of skincare, I like using certain products during certain seasons. This prevents my skin from getting overwhelmed.

Monsoon and excess humidity causes breakouts and when I try to take care of that, skin gets sensitive. So, having a skincare routine that’s gentle is the key here.
